
lets dive into the lib folder which has the main code for the application.

screens — Contains the screens of your application. All files from here get imported into routes.dart
util — Contains the utilities/common functions of your application
widgets — Contains the common widgets for your applications. For example, Button , TextField etc.
routes.dart — Contains the routes of your application and imports all screens.


https://hackernoon.com/scalable-app-structure-in-flutter-dad61a4bc389



lib/
|- main.dart
|- routes.dart
|- screens/
|- util/      -- Util folder contains the business logic of your application. cals, format conversions
|- widgets/   --COMMON Widgets Used Accross Screens
|- data/
|- services/   -- e.g authentication.dart